{"title":"Hub gears for gravel? Sub-£1,000 Hunt × Classified wheelset weighs less than 1,300g","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hunt-classified-powershift-wheels","date":1678438800000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hunt-classified-powershift-wheels\">Hub gears for gravel? Sub-£1,000 Hunt × Classified wheelset weighs less than 1,300g</a></p>\n\n<p>Hunt is the latest in a growing list of brands to partner with internal hub specialists Classified, launching new <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/classified-powershift-hub-review\" target=\"_blank\">Powershift-enabled wheelsets</a> for road and gravel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the likes of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/parcours-classified-powershift-wheels\" target=\"_blank\">Parcours</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/campenaerts-worldtour-classified-powershift-hub\" target=\"_blank\">DT Swiss</a> recently joining the roster, collaborations with the Dutch brand point to the growing popularity of its electronic internal drivetrain system that aims to eliminate the need for a front derailleur.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Hunt x Classified Powershift wheelsets\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_41.jpg 1997w\" /><figcaption>Hunt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Classified says it combines the best of 1× and 2× drivetrains, providing a host of benefits for <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/campenaerts-worldtour-classified-powershift-hub\" target=\"_blank\">amateurs and professional riders alike</a>. Reduced chain force, less risk of dropped chains and ‘instant’ shifting under load are just a few of the claimed advantages of the Powershift system.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hunt has been producing hand-built wheels since 2015, and the brand says a desire to always be ‘looking for opportunities to improve the riding experience through innovation and technology’ was the driving force behind the Classified partnership.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/campenaerts-worldtour-classified-powershift-hub\">Hub gears in the WorldTour: Campenaerts to race on Classified Powershift hub</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/parcours-classified-powershift-wheels\">Parcours becomes first UK brand to bring third-party Classified Powershift wheels to market</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/classified-powershift-hub-review\">Classified Powershift hub review</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Wherever you ride</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_71.jpg 1997w\" /><figcaption>Hunt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hunt × Classified wheelsets draw from Hunt’s existing road and gravel ranges, with one set available from each. The choice for tarmac is the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/hunt-48-limitless-aero-disc-wheelset-review\" target=\"_blank\">48 Limitless Aero disc wheels</a>, which have been ridden to stage victory at the Giro d’Italia. They have a claimed weight of just 1,501g, though this doesn’t include the Powershift internals.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_51.jpg 1997w\" /><figcaption>Hunt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For rougher terrain, the Powershift-enabled technology has been paired with the 40 Carbon Gravel Discs, which Hunt says weigh an impressive 1,270g – though again without the Classified internals – which the brand understandably describes as its ‘featherlight’ wheelset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Riders will need to buy the Powershift Partner kit separately from Classified, which includes the Powershift hub, Smart Thru axle, cassette and shifting unit.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Going the whole hog</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_1-620x413.jpg 620w\" /><figcaption>Hunt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As part of the Classified collaboration, Hunt has also announced that its Powershift-enabled wheels will now be available as an option on Mason Cycles bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘We don’t jump in until we are absolutely sure that a system is proven and there are real-world riding advantages,’ says Dom Mason, founder of Mason Cycles. ‘[Following] the use of it in on gravel bikes, we were very interested to partner with Classified.’</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-647x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2-1140x1710.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/hunt_Classified_wheels_2.jpg 1707w\" /><figcaption>Hunt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the wheels won’t be available to get your hands on until June 2023, Hunt is already taking preorders. The road 48 Limitless wheelset will set you back £1,149 / $1,349 / €1,499, while the 40 Carbon Gravel comes in at £949 / $1,199 / €1,239.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information, head to <a href=\"https://www.huntbikewheels.com/products/classified-x-hunt-40-carbon-gravel-race-wheelset\" target=\"_blank\">Hunt Bike Wheels</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/hunt-classified-powershift-wheels\">Hub gears for gravel? Sub-£1,000 Hunt × Classified wheelset weighs less than 1,300g</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"0fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"3c0dfd89816b800c894497942bb2adcda0e2aae79847a91fd08766","category":"Cycling"}